Plantar fascia

The plantar fascia is a thick aponeurosis running from the calcaneal tuberosity to the the head of each metatarsal bone. There are five bands of tissue tissue beginning at the distal phalanges of each toe, eventually running into and converging near the anteroinferior aspect of the heel. There is one additional band of tissue called the lateral band which comes from the base of the 5th metatarsal and blends into the rest of the tissue of the plantar aponeurosis on the outside edge of the heelbone.
